OL,5, Authors including Sir Michael Morpurgo 
OL,6, and Malorie Blackman have written an   
OL,7, open letter urging the government to   
OL,8, invest in early years reading.         
OL,10,FA BookTrust survey suggests that only  
OL,11,Fhalf of children aged between one and  
OL,12,Ftwo from low-income families are read  
OL,13,Fto daily.                              
OL,15,FThe letter notes that some families    
OL,16,Fstruggle to access books and support.  
OL,18,F"It is not right that children from    
OL,19,Fpoorer backgrounds are deprived of a   
OL,20,Flife that is rich in reading," it says.
